rets and that we must use to the utmost the help provided by scientific method. In this new climate the present book is an indispensable teaching aid."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aAnimal behavior. 0aBehavior, Animal. 0aPsychologie comparée. 0aPsychologie comparée. 0aPsychologie. 0aPsychology, Comparative. 4aMental Disorders. 4aPSYCHOLOGY / General. 4aPsychopathology. 7aMEDICAL / Psychiatry / General.2bisacsh1 aA. Bercel, Nicholas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aA. Lenihan, Ellenora, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlexander, Irving E., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aB. Hollingshead, A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aB. Jackson, Edith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aB. Malmo, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aB. Olinger, Leonard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aB. Raginsky, Bernard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aB. Reed, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aB. Shapiro, Μ., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBellis, Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBettelheim, Bruno, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aC. Redlich, F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aC. Wilkin, Louise, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCaplan, Gerald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aD. Fabing, Howard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aD. Frank, Jerome, eco